119.6	A_Clockwork_Orange	A Clockwork Orange	A Clockwork Orange is a 1962 dystopian novella by Anthony Burgess. The novel contains an experiment in language: the characters often use an argot called "Nadsat", derived from Russian. In 1998, the Modern Library ranked A Clockwork Orange 65th on its list of the 100 best English-language novels of the 20th century.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/23/Clockwork_orange.jpg
